The paper discusses the impact of low bitwidth quantization on the adversarial robustness of neural networks for image classification tasks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the vulnerabilities of neural networks to adversarial attacks, which falls under the category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Finally, the paper proposes an ensemble-based defense mechanism, which falls under the category of cs.SY (Systems and Control).
